                                                                      Python Conditional Statement


 1> if Statement
= The if statement is used to execute a block of code only
  when a condition is True.

  Example:
  age = 20
 if age >= 18:
  print("You can vote")

 2> if-else Statement
= The if-else statement ececute one block of code when
   the condition is True and another ondition is false.

3> if-elif-else Statement

 = The if-elif-else statement is used to check
   miltiple conditions.

 # Key point
 
 elif means else if.

 Python checks condition from top to bottom.

 Once a condition becomes True, the remaining condition
 are skipped.

 4> Nested if

= A Nested if means writting one if statement
  inside another if statement.

 # Key Points
  
 The inner if executes only if the outer if is True.
 
  Useful when multiple condition depend
  on each other.

